list.item:
Confrontation has speeded the deterioration of the Indonesian economy. The
                        most serious short-term problems are growing shortages of foodstuffs and
                        other consumer necessities, and a heavy balance of payments deficit;
                        prospects for improvement are not bright. The political impact has thus far
                        been slight, but if food shortages persist, the problem of maintaining
                        public order in urban areas could become serious. (Paras. 17–2)
